{"nodes":[{"content":"Clipboard cmdlets","pos":[2,19]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Get-Clipboard<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Set-Clipboard<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> make it easier for you to transfer content to and from a Windows PowerShell session.","pos":[20,144],"source":"**Get-Clipboard** and **Set-Clipboard** make it easier for you to transfer content to and from a Windows PowerShell session."},{"content":"For example, if you use Windows Explorer to copy three files to the clipboard (by selecting them and pressing <ph id=\"ph1\">`ctrl-c`</ph>, for example), you can then easily access the contents of the clipboard as a list of files:","pos":[145,355],"source":" For example, if you use Windows Explorer to copy three files\nto the clipboard (by selecting them and pressing `ctrl-c`, for example), you can then easily access the contents of the clipboard as a list of files:"},{"content":"The Clipboard cmdlets support images, audio files, file lists, and text.","pos":[651,723]}],"content":"# Clipboard cmdlets\n**Get-Clipboard** and **Set-Clipboard** make it easier for you to transfer content to and from a Windows PowerShell session. For example, if you use Windows Explorer to copy three files\nto the clipboard (by selecting them and pressing `ctrl-c`, for example), you can then easily access the contents of the clipboard as a list of files:\n\n```powershell \nPS C:\\\\&gt; Get-Clipboard -Format FileDropList\n\nDirectory: C:\\\\Users\\\\slee\\\\Downloads\\\\Example\n\nMode LastWriteTime Length Name\n\n---- ------------- ------ ----\n\n-a---- 4/14/2015 1:19 PM 0 File2.txt\n\n-a---- 4/14/2015 1:19 PM 0 File3.txt\n\n-a---- 4/14/2015 1:19 PM 0 File1.txt\n```\n\n\nThe Clipboard cmdlets support images, audio files, file lists, and text.\n"}